=  An Asiidoc guide
Viivi Mustonen <viivi.mk.mustonen@gmail.com>
v1.0, 2021-03-20

In this guide I will tell you about the Asciidoc markup technique. 

== Paragraphs

Paragraphs don't have special markup,they are defined by one or more consecutive lines. 

There should be at least one blank line when a new paragraphh begins.

This is a normal paragraph that follows source format rules.

===  Text styles
These are text styles, used to define word meanings.

* normal text, _italicized_, *bolded*, +monotext+.
* ``double quotes'', `single quote'.
* normal, ^super text^, ~sub text~.
* `passthrough *bolded*`

====Tables and lists

.This is an example table
[options="header,footer"]
|=======================
|Col 1|Col 2      |Col 3
|1    |Item 1     |a
|2    |Item 2     |b
|3    |Item 3     |c
|6    |Three items|d
|===

====This is a list

.List title
* list subject 1
** nested list item
*** double nested list item 1
*** double nested list item 2
* list subject 2
|===

Tables

.This is an example table
|===
|Column heading 1 |Column heading 2

|Column 1, row 1
|Column 2, row 1

|Column 1, row 2
|Column 2, row 2
|===

Lists

Lists in aciidoc are unordered or ordered.

Unordered list

* Level 1 list item
** Level 2 list item
*** Level 3 list item
**** Level 4 list item
***** Level 5 list item
* Level 1 list item

Ordered list

. Level 1 list item
.. Level 2 list item
... Level 3 list item
.... Level 4 list item
..... Level 5 list item
. Level 1 list item

Checklist

* [*] checked
* [x] also checked
* [ ] not checked
* normal list item

===== Comments and block titles
Comments

// This is a single-line comment

////
This is a multi-line comment.

Block title

.This is an example block title
====
This is content in a block title. Normal style rules apply
====

